# Go coding standards

This Cursor rule mirrors the `go-coding` router skill — apply it when editing Go. Two principles:

- **Deterministic beats prose** — whatever a formatter or linter enforces, run the tool; don't
  hand-derive it.
- **Don't rebuild code intelligence** — use `gopls` (the `gopls-lsp` plugin) for
  defs/refs/diagnostics/rename/vulncheck.

| Topic | Run (deterministic) | Deeper skill |
|---|---|---|
| Formatting | `gofmt`/`gofumpt` (+ `goimports`) — machine-enforced | — |
| Static analysis / bugs | `go vet ./...`, `golangci-lint run` | `go-linting` |
| Modern idioms | `golangci-lint run --enable-only=modernize`, `go fix ./...` | `go-idioms` |
| Errors | `golangci-lint run --enable-only=errorlint` | `go-errors` |
| Concurrency | `go test -race ./...`, `go vet ./...` | `go-concurrency` |
| Testing | `go test -race ./...`; `testing/synctest` (1.25) for time/concurrency | `go-testing` |
| Layout | judgment | `go-layout` |

Ground every judgment call in a cited source — Effective Go, Go Code Review Comments, the Google
and Uber Go style guides, `pkg.go.dev`. Don't invent rules. Adopt the shipped golangci-lint v2
config (`references/golangci.v2.yml`, at the **plugin root** — resolve via `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/references/…` or Glob the installed copy, not under this rule's dir); run `golangci-lint run --fix` for auto-fixable findings.
